      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake the sponge",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional. Grease and line two 23 cm round tins. Beat the butter and brown sugar together until fluffy. Beat in the maple syrup, then the eggs one at a time. Fold in the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and nutmeg in alternation with the milk. Fold in the toasted pecans. Divide between the tins and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool on racks.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the frosting and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the cream cheese and butter until smooth. Add the sifted icing sugar in two additions and beat until thick. Beat in the maple syrup. If the frosting is too soft, refrigerate for 15 minutes. Place the first layer on a serving plate and spread with one third of the frosting. Top with the second layer and cover the top and sides with the remaining frosting. Arrange the pecan halves over the top.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
